cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on QoS and resource management in converged networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper presents a policy-based network management paradigm and distributed functional entities for resource coordination. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possibility as the paper may discuss security considerations in QoS and resource management. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as the paper may discuss distributed resource management. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is a possibility as the paper may discuss performance evaluation of the CNQF framework.
